## Heroku

<img src="<%= url_for '/images/heroku.png' %>" width="96" height="96" alt=
"Heroku" class="image-float-right" style="border-radius: 8px">

Looking to deploy to Heroku? The way to use Passenger on Heroku is through [the Standalone mode](https://www.phusionpassenger.com/documentation/Users%20guide%20Standalone.html). Invoke <code>passenger start</code> in your Procfile as web server.

Please take a look at our [Heroku demo for Ruby](https://github.com/phusion/passenger-ruby-heroku-demo) for an example.

## Troubleshooting

When you run Passenger in production, there are times when you can run into trouble. If that happens, please refer to one of the troubleshooting guides:

 * [**Nginx** mode troubleshooting](https://www.phusionpassenger.com/documentation/Users%20guide%20Nginx.html#troubleshooting)
 * [**Apache** mode troubleshooting](https://www.phusionpassenger.com/documentation/Users%20guide%20Apache.html#troubleshooting)
 * [**Standalone** mode troubleshooting](https://www.phusionpassenger.com/documentation/Users%20guide%20Standalone.html#troubleshooting)

